<http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3792316>
    bibo:endPage "96" ;
    bibo:issue "9" ;
    bibo:journal "ZooKeys" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2009-05-12" ;
    bibo:startPage "89" ;
    bibo:volume "9" ;
    dc:creator "Schmidt, Christian" ;
    dc:date "2009" ;
    dc:title "A new genus and two new species of arctiine tiger moth (Noctuidae, Arctiinae, Arctiini) from Costa Rica" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3810733>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3810741>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3810737> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3810733>
    dc:description "Figures 1-2. Adult habitus of Leichosila gen. n. 1. Leichosila talamanca sp. n., male holotype. 2. Leichosila wagneri sp. n., male holotype." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3810733/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3810741>
    dc:description "Figures 6-9. Structural features of Leichosila. 6. L. talamanca, uncus (dorsal view); 7. L. wagneri, uncus (dorsal view); 8. L. talamanca, juxta; 9. L. talamanca, antenna (segments 14 – 18), ventral view (setae and cilia omitted except on segment 14)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3810741/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3810737>
    dc:description "Figures 3-5. Male genitalia of Leichosila. 3a. L. talamanca (paratype), genital capsule (ventral view); 3b. phallus (left lateral view), with inflated vesica (ventrobasal diverticulum highlighted); 4a. L. wagneri (holotype), genital capsule (ventral view); 4b. phallus (left lateral view) with inflated vesica (ventrobasal diverticulum highlighted); 5. L. talamanca, 8th abdominal sternite, showing medioventral sclerite and lateral lobes." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3810737/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

